Welcome To Triaxis GNU/Linux Handbook x86
This Guide Will Help You To Install Triaxis Correctly

1 Download Ubuntu Server 16.04 Here https://releases.ubuntu.com/16.04/
2 Then Select Server install image 32-bit PC (i386) server install image
3 When You On Live Iso Press F6 The Select Expert Mode Then Setup Ubuntu Server
4 After You Install

Run sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

Run sudo nano /etc/os-release
Then Change Ubuntu To Triaxis GNU/Linux
Example

NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux X86"
ID=triaxis
ID_LIKE=debian
BUILD_ID=rolling
PRETTY_NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux X86"
HOME_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux"
SUPPORT_URL=
BUG_REPORT_URL=

Keep The Support URL Bug Report URL And Privacy Policy URL Ubuntu

Then sudo nano /etc/issue
Then Change Ubuntu (Version Name LTS) \n \l To Triaxis GNU/Linux X86 \n \l
CTRL X Y ENTER

Then sudo nano /etc/issue.net
Then Change Ubuntu (Version Name LTS) To Triaxis GNU/Linux X86
CTRL X Y ENTER

Change Grub If You Need It Run sudo nano /etc/default/grub then
GRUB_TIMEOUT=0
Change them to:
GRUB_TIMEOUT=5
update grub using sudo update-grub
Change GRUB Distributor Name Ubuntu To Triaxis Change it to: GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Triaxis X86"
Then Update grub using sudo update-grub

Reboot using sudo reboot

5 You May Stop The Services Of Snap
  sudo systemctl stop snapd
  sudo systemctl disable snapd

6 Purge Snapd (Recommended For Older Hardware Or Any Slow Hardware)
  sudo apt purge snapd

7 Clean Up Leftover Directories
  rm -rf ~/snap
  sudo rm -rf /var/snap /var/lib/snapd /var/cache/snapd

8 Reboot
  sudo reboot

9  System Updates: Ubuntu may reinstall Snapd during major upgrades. To prevent this, you can block Snapd from being reinstalled:
   sudo apt-mark hold snapd

10 Run sudo update-initramfs -u

Have Fun And Start Using Triaxis x86
